      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-level2",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was conducted using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the scalar transport equation used for the hemolysis power-law model. Observed order of convergence (OOC) for velocity components: 1.94–2.01 (expected 2nd order); OOC for hemolysis scalar: 1.88. All results within 5% of theoretical order. Additionally, benchmark comparisons against the FDA Critical Path nozzle dataset and lid-driven cavity solutions confirm correct implementation. Level 3 achieved (OOC demonstrated plus benchmark suite); required level 2.",
