      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against experimental measurements performed using the U95 validation metric per ASME V&V 20. Experimental uncertainty U_D (combined systematic and random, 95% CI): ±11.4% of mean NIH. Simulation numerical uncertainty U_num: ±3.4%. Validation metric E = (D - S)/D: range −0.082 to +0.094 across 5 operating points. All |E| < U_val = sqrt(U_D² + U_num²) = 11.9%. Model passes the V&V 20 validation criterion at all operating points. Validation comparison plots with uncertainty bars included in evidence package. Level 3 criterion (quantitative metric with uncertainty budget) met.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/validation-run-nominal-2025-11",
