      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest (QoI) is the Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH), which is the same metric used in the regulatory submission and clinical threshold specification. NIH is computed from the same scalar transport hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen et al., modified Zhang coefficients) in both the validation simulations and the COU predictions. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) were also validated and show consistent agreement. The mapping between computational QoI and clinical decision threshold is explicit and documented in the requirements traceability matrix. Level 3 achieved: QoI identity between validation and COU is demonstrated with full traceability.",
