      "rationale": "Iterative convergence of the steady-periodic CFD solution was assessed at each operating point. Residuals for continuity, momentum, and hemolysis scalar all converge to below 1×10⁻⁵ (normalized). Cycle-to-cycle variation in NIH between final two impeller revolutions: <0.3%. Floating-point precision: double (64-bit) throughout. Round-off error estimated as negligible relative to discretization error (ratio <0.01). Solver settings (relaxation factors, linear solver tolerances) are documented in the simulation input files archived in the evidence package. Level 2 criterion (documented convergence to specified tolerance) met.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/solver-convergence-check-2025-11"
    },
    {
