      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Use error controls include: (1) a documented simulation execution procedure (SEP) with step-by-step checklist for mesh generation, boundary condition assignment, solver configuration, and post-processing; (2) independent peer review of all simulation input files by a second qualified CFD analyst; (3) automated pre-simulation input validation script that checks boundary condition completeness, mesh quality metrics (max skewness <0.82, min orthogonality >15°), and turbulence model parameter ranges; (4) post-simulation automated QA checks for mass conservation (imbalance <0.01%) and energy balance. All five COU operating point simulations passed all automated checks. Level 3 achieved (SEP plus independent review plus automated checks); required Level 2.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/use-error-review-2025-11"
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
