      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level3",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment addresses: (1) turbulence modeling — SST k-ω selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating machinery flows; sensitivity study comparing SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and RSM shows NIH variation <6% across models, with SST k-ω closest to experimental data; (2) hemolysis model — power-law scalar transport (Zhang 2011 coefficients) validated against 47 literature data points for simple shear and extensional flows (R²=0.89); (3) non-Newtonian blood rheology — Carreau-Yasuda model included; sensitivity study shows <2% NIH difference vs. Newtonian at COU shear rates; (4) geometric fidelity — full pump geometry including volute, impeller passages, and gaps modeled; clearance gap mesh confirmed adequate. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% NIH and included in UQ budget. Level 3 criterion met.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/model-form-assessment-2025-09",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/model-form-uncertainty-estimate"
