      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "All model inputs are documented with sources and uncertainty estimates. Geometric inputs: CAD model from manufacturer with dimensional inspection report (GD&T, ±0.05 mm). Fluid properties: blood analog viscosity from rheometer measurements (3.5 ± 0.2 cP), density from pycnometer (1050 ± 5 kg/m³). Boundary conditions: inlet flow rate from Coriolis flowmeter calibration data, rotational speed from encoder. Hemolysis model coefficients (α=3.62×10⁻⁷, β=2.416, C=0.785) from Zhang (2011) with documented uncertainty ranges. Monte Carlo UQ propagates all input uncertainties through the model (1000 samples). Input uncertainty contributions to NIH output uncertainty are rank-ordered via Sobol indices. Level 3 criterion (all inputs with documented uncertainty and UQ propagation) met.",
