      "rationale": "Validation test samples (blood analog fluid batches) were prepared and characterized per ASTM F1841 (Standard Practice for Assessment of Hemolysis in Continuous Flow Blood Pumps). Three independent fluid batches used across the experimental campaign; inter-batch variability in NIH: ±3.2%. Each batch characterized for hematocrit, viscosity, and initial plasma hemoglobin. Sample preparation, handling, and storage protocols documented. Number of independent experimental replicates: n=5 per operating point. Statistical analysis: mean, standard deviation, and 95% CI reported for each operating point. Level 3 achieved (multiple independent samples with full characterization and statistical analysis); required Level 2.",
