      "rationale": "A formal parameter equivalency analysis was performed comparing the validation test configuration to the COU. Key non-dimensional parameters assessed: Reynolds number (Re_val = 1.35–2.05×10⁵ vs. Re_COU = 1.28–2.12×10⁵, overlap >95% of COU range), flow coefficient (Φ_val = 0.079–0.143 vs. Φ_COU = 0.081–0.141), specific speed (Ns identical, same pump archetype), and hemolysis exposure parameter (scalar transport Péclet number within 4% across all operating points). Fluid property equivalency: viscosity ratio within 3%, density within 0.5%. Geometric equivalency: same CAD model used for both validation simulations and COU predictions. Parameter equivalency table included in evidence package with quantitative similarity metrics. Level 3 criterion (quantitative non-dimensional parameter matching with documented similarity) met.",
